Description: Do not treat warnings as errors in the vendored Fast DDS library build
 Fedora injects -Werror via CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_INIT, turning benign upstream
 warnings (unused-but-set variables in CacheChange.hpp, the bundled sqlite3
 amalgamation, etc.) into hard errors on Fedora's GCC. Add
 add_compile_options(-Wno-error) at the top of the library's own CMakeLists so
 it is applied after the inherited flags and overrides -Werror for the fastdds
 target. Upstream keeps -Werror only in its own CI.
Origin: vendor-specific
Forwarded: not-needed, downstream packaging relaxation of warnings-as-errors
Last-Update: 2026-06-03
--- a/src/cpp/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 20:52:25.050197655 -0500
+++ b/src/cpp/CMakeLists.txt	2026-06-02 20:52:25.061007316 -0500
@@ -12,6 +12,10 @@
 # See the License for the specific language governing permissions and
 # limitations under the License.
 
+# Fedora injects -Werror (via CMAKE_CXX_FLAGS_INIT); relax it for this
+# vendored library target so benign upstream warnings do not fail the build.
+add_compile_options($<$<COMPILE_LANGUAGE:CXX>:-Wno-error>)
+
 include(CheckCXXSourceCompiles)
 
 # Set source files
